    feat: async runtime and concurrent minting orchestration (noscope-5dw)
    
    Implement parallel multi-provider minting using tokio as the async runtime.
    
    The orchestrator module (src/orchestrator.rs) provides:
    - mint_all(): async function that executes provider mint operations in parallel
      with bounded concurrency and per-provider timeouts
    - format_orchestrator_output(): converts CredentialSet to JSON array via
      format_mint_output()
    
    Rules covered:
    - NS-050: Bounded parallelism via tokio::sync::Semaphore (max_concurrent)
    - NS-046: Per-provider timeout via tokio::time::timeout
    - NS-006: Atomic rollback via resolve_mint_results() (all-or-nothing)
    - NS-047: Succeeded tokens returned for rollback when any provider fails
    - NS-063: JSON array output wired through format_mint_output()
    
    Also adds CredentialSet::tokens() iterator for envelope construction.

